Sentencas: Anode-supported cone-shaped tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are successfully fabricated by a phase inversion method.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: During processing, the two opposite sides of each cone-shaped anode tube are in different conditions-one side is in contact with coagulant (the corresponding surface is named as W-surface), while the other is isolated from coagulate (I-surface).
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: Single SOFCs are made with YSZ electrolyte membrane coated on either W-surface or I-surface.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: Compared to the cell with YSZ membrane on W-surface, the cell on I-surface exhibits better performance, giving a maximum power density of 350 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, using wet hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: AC impedance test results are consistent with the performance.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: The sectional and surface structures of the SOFCs were examined by SEM and the relationship between SOFC performance and anode structure is analyzed.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion

Sentencas: Structure of anodes fabricated at different phase inversion temperature is also investigated.
Titulo: Effect of anode structure on performance of cone-shaped solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by phase inversion
